Durban - A  Pietermaritzburg man who was shot in the leg and found lying on the pavement has been taken to hospital. While the circumstances surrounding the shooting is unknown at this stage, Mountain Rise SAPS were on scene. Spokesperson for ER24 Russel Meiring said when paramedics arrived on scene they found the man lying on the pavement on Old Greytown Road. "Paramedics assessed the man and found that he had sustained a gunshot wound to his lower leg." Meiring said the man was treated for his injury and later transported to Northdale Provincial Hospital for further care. "The motive for the incident is unknown at this stage. Local authorities will be conducting an investigation into the incident." According to News 24, a Pietermaritzburg couple escaped unscathed when stray bullets hit their home in Northdale. It is alleged that one bullet went through the tiles missing the couple. The matter had not been reported to the police. POST